<figureCitation box="[538,565,1344,1368]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="6.[189,241,1452,1476]" captionTargetBox="[438,1194,219,1406]" captionTargetId="figure-221@6.[438,1194,218,1406]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs. 20–22. Distribution maps of five Perlesta species in western Maryland, USA, based on material examined during this study. 20, P. ephelida; 21, P. nelsoni, P. placida, and P. MD sp. 5; 22, P. teaysia. MD = Maryland, VA = Virginia, WV = West Virginia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4761246" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4761246/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">21</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[189,798,1415,1907]" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,283,1415,1439]" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Female.</emphasis>
Forewing length 9.5–11.0 mm (n = 3). Head light pale yellow with a golden brown intraocellar patch that is slightly open anteriorly, plus a light golden-brown triangular patch anterior to the anterior ocellus; m-line indistinguishable (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="1.[189,241,1500,1524]" captionTargetBox="[286,1344,254,1453]" captionTargetId="figure-161@1.[286,1344,254,1453]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs. 1–6. Perlesta sp. MD-5, Maryland, Sideling Hill Creek. 1–2, female, head + pronotum, dorsal profile; 3, entire egg, 300X; 4, egg, posterior pole, 500X; 5, egg, posterior pole and collar, 2300X; 6, egg, anterior pole and micropyles, 600X." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4761236" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4761236/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Figs. 1– 2</figureCitation>
). Pronotum light golden brown with no medial stripe (
<figureCitation box="[272,377,1631,1656]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="1.[189,241,1500,1524]" captionTargetBox="[286,1344,254,1453]" captionTargetId="figure-161@1.[286,1344,254,1453]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs. 1–6. Perlesta sp. MD-5, Maryland, Sideling Hill Creek. 1–2, female, head + pronotum, dorsal profile; 3, entire egg, 300X; 4, egg, posterior pole, 500X; 5, egg, posterior pole and collar, 2300X; 6, egg, anterior pole and micropyles, 600X." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4761236" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4761236/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Figs. 1–2</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate ca. ½ width of 8 
<superScript attach="right" box="[783,798,1632,1646]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">th</superScript>
abdominal sternum, lacking pigmentation. Lobes distinct, rounded laterally, bordered by a v-shaped notch.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[189,798,1415,1907]" lastBlockId="2.[835,1444,227,972]" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,241,1775,1799]" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Egg.</emphasis>
Oval (
<figureCitation box="[325,394,1775,1799]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="1.[189,241,1500,1524]" captionTargetBox="[286,1344,254,1453]" captionTargetId="figure-161@1.[286,1344,254,1453]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs. 1–6. Perlesta sp. MD-5, Maryland, Sideling Hill Creek. 1–2, female, head + pronotum, dorsal profile; 3, entire egg, 300X; 4, egg, posterior pole, 500X; 5, egg, posterior pole and collar, 2300X; 6, egg, anterior pole and micropyles, 600X." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4761236" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4761236/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). Collar small and straight-sided, raised about chorionic surface, flange lacking (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="1.[189,241,1500,1524]" captionTargetBox="[286,1344,254,1453]" captionTargetId="figure-161@1.[286,1344,254,1453]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs. 1–6. Perlesta sp. MD-5, Maryland, Sideling Hill Creek. 1–2, female, head + pronotum, dorsal profile; 3, entire egg, 300X; 4, egg, posterior pole, 500X; 5, egg, posterior pole and collar, 2300X; 6, egg, anterior pole and micropyles, 600X." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4761236" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4761236/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Figs. 4–5</figureCitation>
); chorion covered by a patchwork of amoeboidlike polygons (
<figureCitation box="[378,498,1883,1907]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="1.[189,241,1500,1524]" captionTargetBox="[286,1344,254,1453]" captionTargetId="figure-161@1.[286,1344,254,1453]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs. 1–6. Perlesta sp. MD-5, Maryland, Sideling Hill Creek. 1–2, female, head + pronotum, dorsal profile; 3, entire egg, 300X; 4, egg, posterior pole, 500X; 5, egg, posterior pole and collar, 2300X; 6, egg, anterior pole and micropyles, 600X." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4761236" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4761236/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Figs. 4, 6</figureCitation>
); micropyles present in anterior ¼ (
<figureCitation box="[972,1039,228,252]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="1.[189,241,1500,1524]" captionTargetBox="[286,1344,254,1453]" captionTargetId="figure-161@1.[286,1344,254,1453]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs. 1–6. Perlesta sp. MD-5, Maryland, Sideling Hill Creek. 1–2, female, head + pronotum, dorsal profile; 3, entire egg, 300X; 4, egg, posterior pole, 500X; 5, egg, posterior pole and collar, 2300X; 6, egg, anterior pole and micropyles, 600X." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4761236" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4761236/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
