<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="67" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[835,1444,227,972]" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[835,950,444,468]" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Remarks.</emphasis>
The eggs appear different from all other species of eastern Nearctic 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Banks" authorityYear="1906" box="[1226,1311,480,504]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Perlesta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1226,1311,480,504]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Perlesta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. A brief description was provided here in hope that females can be associated with males at some point in the future. These eggs may pertain to one of three 
<taxonomicName box="[835,1011,624,648]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Perlesta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[835,921,624,648]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Perlesta</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
whose eggs are unknown and found along the Atlantic Coastal Plain region of 
<collectingRegion box="[1346,1443,660,684]" country="United States of America" name="Virginia" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Virginia</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[886,1070,696,720]" country="United States of America" name="North Carolina" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">North Carolina</collectingRegion>
: 
<taxonomicName authority="Kondratieff, Zuellig &amp; Lenat, 2011" authorityName="Kondratieff, Zuellig &amp; Lenat" authorityYear="2011" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Perlesta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="beatyi">
<emphasis box="[1080,1174,696,720]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">P. beatyi</emphasis>
Kondratieff, Zuellig &amp; Lenat, 2011
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Kondratieff &amp; Kirchner, 2006" authorityName="Kondratieff &amp; Kirchner" authorityYear="2006" box="[980,1439,732,756]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Perlesta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bjostadi">
<emphasis box="[980,1092,732,756]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">P. bjostadi</emphasis>
Kondratieff &amp; Kirchner, 2006
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Kondratieff, Zuellig &amp; Kirchner, 2008" authorityName="Kondratieff, Zuellig &amp; Kirchner" authorityYear="2008" box="[887,1440,768,792]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Perlesta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="durfeei">
<emphasis box="[887,990,768,792]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">P. durfeei</emphasis>
Kondratieff, Zuellig &amp; Kirchner, 2008
</taxonomicName>
. The egg of 
<taxonomicName authority="Kondratieff &amp; Zuellig, 2006" authorityName="Kondratieff &amp; Zuellig" authorityYear="2006" box="[963,1443,804,828]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Perlesta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leathermani">
<emphasis box="[963,1118,804,828]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">P. leathermani</emphasis>
Kondratieff &amp; Zuellig, 2006
</taxonomicName>
also has a small, “button- like” collar (their 
<figureCitation box="[1355,1424,840,864]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="3.[189,241,1497,1521]" captionTargetBox="[286,1344,254,1451]" captionTargetId="figure-197@3.[286,1344,254,1452]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs. 7–12. Perlesta mihucorum, male, Maryland, Conococheague Creek; 7, head + pronotum, dorsal profile; 8, paraprocts, lateral view, 250X; 9, paraprocts, dorsal view, 300X; 10, paraprocts, caudal view, 230X; 11, aedeagus, dorsolateral view, 250X; 12, aedeagus, dorsal view, 250X." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4761238" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4761238/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
.). The light head pigmentation of MD-5 (
<figureCitation box="[1321,1429,876,900]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="1.[189,241,1500,1524]" captionTargetBox="[286,1344,254,1453]" captionTargetId="figure-161@1.[286,1344,254,1453]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs. 1–6. Perlesta sp. MD-5, Maryland, Sideling Hill Creek. 1–2, female, head + pronotum, dorsal profile; 3, entire egg, 300X; 4, egg, posterior pole, 500X; 5, egg, posterior pole and collar, 2300X; 6, egg, anterior pole and micropyles, 600X." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4761236" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4761236/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Figs. 1–2</figureCitation>
), however, appears different from the darker 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kondratieff &amp; Zuellig" authorityYear="2006" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Perlesta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leathermani">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">P. leathermani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Kondratieff et al. 2006, their 
<figureCitation box="[1312,1375,948,972]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="1.[189,241,1500,1524]" captionTargetBox="[286,1344,254,1453]" captionTargetId="figure-161@1.[286,1344,254,1453]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs. 1–6. Perlesta sp. MD-5, Maryland, Sideling Hill Creek. 1–2, female, head + pronotum, dorsal profile; 3, entire egg, 300X; 4, egg, posterior pole, 500X; 5, egg, posterior pole and collar, 2300X; 6, egg, anterior pole and micropyles, 600X." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4761236" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4761236/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
